'''Society for the Promotion of Life-Cycle Analysis''' (SPOLD) was the association of multiple companies that wanted to create an file format that would help mold Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) software into a better management tool. The SPOLD format, which was created for this task, was meant to be implemented in LCA software so that it could exchange more reliable data in inventories.<ref name="Cahn1994">{{cite book|author=Arno Cahn|title=Proceedings of the 3rd World Conference on Detergents: Global Perspectives|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pbr2HJ1X_DkC&pg=PA62|date=30 January 1994|publisher=The American Oil Chemists Society|isbn=978-0-935315-52-3|pages=62–|quote=Indeed, the broad view provided by an LCA reveals strengths and weaknesses in comparison to competing or potential substitutes. ... This is the exact purpose of a new Brussels-based coalition, created a year ago, under the name of Society for the Promotion of LCA Development (SPOLD). The science base of the LCA methodology cannot be compromised because it needs ...}}</ref><ref name="Nath1998">{{cite book|author=Bhaskar Nath|title=Environmental Management in Practice: Instruments for Environmental Management|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xV7IlSKjq-QC&pg=PA213|year=1998|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-415-14906-8|pages=213–|quote=Notably, the Society for the Promotion of LCA Development (SPOLD), whose membership includes large industrial companies, has been funding research projects on LCA. One of the specific aims of SPOLD is to design a common format for ...}}</ref><ref name="Agioutantis2003">{{cite book|author=Zacharias Agioutantis|title=Book of proceedings|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FCNCcCY_pzIC&pg=PA135|year=2003|publisher=Heliotopos Conferences|isbn=978-960-87054-2-5|pages=135–|quote=The development of LCA methodology in Europe has been further promoted by the Society for the Promotion of LCA Development (SPOLD) and a number of EU initiatives such as the European network